Dialogue: 10,0:01:36.79,0:01:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ph-Phantom...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:07.28,0:02:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.48,0:02:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yazawa? It's me, Matsuki.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:10.54,0:02:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:11.44,0:02:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm in town. Can we meet?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:13.84,0:02:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I don't want to see anyone right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:16.82,0:02:20.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I pushed back my return to Japan \Na whole day just to see you.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:20.31,0:02:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I'm already at the bar \Nin front of your hotel. I'll wait.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:26.10,0:02:28.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's been two months since I saw Matsuki.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:28.71,0:02:33.34,Thought,,0,0,0,,We've known each other since high school. \NWe both loved the sky.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:34.68,0:02:40.66,Thought,,0,0,0,,He became editor-in-chief of an aviation magazine\N called {\i0}Air Journal{\i1}, and I became a pilot.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:41.33,0:02:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Coke.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:42.85,0:02:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Same as always. Hard to believe \Na guy like you doesn't touch alcohol.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:47.73,0:02:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,How'd you find me? Sachiko?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:50.56,0:02:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. You just up and disappeared\N from Japan without a word.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:00.16,0:03:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Sachiko-san was worried.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:03.67,0:03:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,After the accident, you were restless \Nthe whole time you were in the hospital. {/irritated}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:07.58,0:03:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Then one day you made up your mind about something, like you'd seen things crystal clear.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:13.15,0:03:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why you retired \Nfrom the Air Self-Defense Force.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:17.39,0:03:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:19.06,0:03:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to know why I retired?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:31.03,0:03:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,A Phantom?!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:33.40,0:03:38.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. One flew over El Salvador \Nand bombed some guerrillas.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:38.35,0:03:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,No way. The US hasn't officially supplied \NPhantoms to El Salvador.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:43.60,0:03:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Not officially, at least.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:45.18,0:03:48.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, how about going to El Salvador? \NI'll make it worth your while.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:48.50,0:03:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You want me to investigate it?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.33,0:03:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,A cameraman named Taniguchi \Nshot this over there. {in el salvador}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:54.11,0:03:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,He wants a jet expert.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:56.65,0:04:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,This could be the scoop of a lifetime. \NTeam up with him and dig out the truth.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.80,0:04:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You think I'd take that job?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:08.36,0:04:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yazawa.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.33,0:04:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,When you flew the Phantom \Nin the Self-Defense Forces...
Dialogue: 10,0:04:16.99,0:04:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,were you ever a real fighter pilot?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:28.46,0:04:30.45,Thought,,0,0,0,,Matsuki knew.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:30.45,0:04:35.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,After that accident, something had taken root inside me. It was the sky.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:39.51,0:04:42.70,Song,,0,0,0,,I'm ready for the journey to the space {THE STRANGER (FLY THE NIGHT) - fully lyrics from collectr's CD pics}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:42.70,0:04:47.83,Song,,0,0,0,,Shooting to the darkness sky and victories
Dialogue: 10,0:04:50.27,0:04:53.70,Song,,0,0,0,,I've got silver wing and nothing to scare
Dialogue: 10,0:04:53.72,0:04:59.91,Song,,0,0,0,,Unlimited the black hole to my head
Dialogue: 10,0:05:01.90,0:05:05.26,Song,,0,0,0,,Make me feel right \NIt's coming to fight now {I hear 'to fight'}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:05.27,0:05:07.80,Song,,0,0,0,,Make me so high \NIt's running away
Dialogue: 10,0:05:07.81,0:05:10.75,Song,,0,0,0,,Take me to the sky make me so high
Dialogue: 10,0:05:11.18,0:05:14.20,Song,,0,0,0,,I wanna fly the night
Dialogue: 10,0:05:14.21,0:05:16.16,Song,,0,0,0,,Make me feel right \NIt's coming fight now
Dialogue: 10,0:05:16.17,0:05:18.80,Song,,0,0,0,,Make me so high \NIt's running away
Dialogue: 10,0:05:18.82,0:05:22.17,Song,,0,0,0,,Take me to the sky\N Make me so high
Dialogue: 10,0:05:22.97,0:05:29.86,Song,,0,0,0,,Strangers fly the night
Dialogue: 10,0:05:29.87,0:05:37.20,Song,,0,0,0,,The night! {probably}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:40.88,0:04:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Iwaoka! Eject! Iwaoka!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:45.81,0:04:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Iwaoka!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:01.91,0:05:06.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,It was a maintenance failure. \NThe crash wasn't our fault.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:06.31,0:05:10.73,Thought,,0,0,0,,But the facts were buried inside \Nthe Self-Defense Forces and hidden from the public.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:10.73,0:05:15.83,Thought,,0,0,0,,I was seriously injured and hovered \Nbetween life and death for six months.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:52.75,0:05:58.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,In San Salvador, the capital \Nof El Salvador, I met Taniguchi.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:58.48,0:06:01.95,Thought,,0,0,0,,He and I were scheduled to meet two pilots
Dialogue: 10,0:06:01.95,0:06:07.67,Thought,,0,0,0,,from Ilopango Air Base at a small bar\N about ten kilometers from town.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:27.70,0:06:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,They're being extremely cagey. \NThey won't share many details.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:36.80,0:06:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:37.54,0:06:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems certain a new fighter arrived\N at the base about a month ago.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:42.11,0:06:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They gave us this.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:53.46,0:06:55.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,It was unmistakably a Phantom.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.89,0:07:01.15,Thought,,0,0,0,,What's more, it bore the serial number\N of Japan's Air Self-Defense Force 7th Air Wing.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:01.55,0:07:04.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,My old unit.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:10.33,0:07:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Military police. Damn it!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:13.36,0:07:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I paid them too much and someone noticed.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:16.01,0:07:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's move.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.29,0:07:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it! It's too dangerous \Nto stay together. Let's split up!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:33.26,0:07:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Right!
Dialogue: 10,0:07:42.07,0:07:44.84,Top,,0,0,0,,The Jap target appears to have fled
Dialogue: 10,0:07:44.84,0:07:47.57,Top,,0,0,0,,into the jungle northwest of Santa Ana. {not sure how he got there from san salvador but that's what he says}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:53.29,0:07:54.67,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in pursuit?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:54.67,0:07:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:56.50,0:07:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The negatives?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:57.87,0:08:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Secured from the pilots as ordered. \NAnd from the Japanese cameraman.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:04.32,0:08:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Add two more companies to the Jap's pursuit.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:07.84,0:08:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Vincent, with all due respect, \Ncommitting more troops to a single Jap...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:14.31,0:08:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Turner, what orders did you receive from Langley?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:20.86,0:08:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Get the dogs ready.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:22.38,0:08:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:23.78,0:08:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Dogs will capture the target faster \Nthan this country's useless soldiers.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:29.41,0:08:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And have a helicopter ready in ten minutes. \NI'm going out myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:33.49,0:08:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Vincent...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:36.21,0:08:41.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is Langley taking one Jap so seriously?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:41.06,0:08:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll ask again. What orders were you given?
Dialogue: 10,0:08:44.50,0:08:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes, sir...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:45.65,0:08:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Say it.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:46.98,0:08:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Provide full support for Mr. David Vincent, \Ncase officer of Project Carib One.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:54.47,0:08:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow his instructions and do not inquire\N about the operation's purpose
Dialogue: 10,0:08:59.02,0:09:01.82,Default,,0,0,0,,or any matters concerning him.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:01.82,0:09:02.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Not quite.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:02.81,0:09:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:04.46,0:09:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not that you mustn't ask.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:06.83,0:09:09.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You simply don't {\i1}need{\i0} to know.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.88,0:09:30.72,Thought,,0,0,0,,Why?! Why are they chasing me this far \Njust for that one photograph?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.86,0:09:45.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,The target is close. \NThe dogs are getting excited.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:45.92,0:09:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Which direction are the dogs going?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.42,0:09:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Northwest.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:56.16,0:09:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Pilot, move ahead up the river\N and hover there.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.70,0:10:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:10:22.65,0:10:24.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Crap. {???? shimatta? shimeta?}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:40.54,0:10:44.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,Damn it... He's toying with me.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:44.00,0:10:47.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Good. Keep him pinned down like that.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:56.99,0:10:59.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? He's trying to shoot back? {?????}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:59.18,0:11:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the call?! \NDo we take the shot?! {/aim at him}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:01.30,0:11:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Hold.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.27,0:11:06.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He's taking a gamble.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:14.82,0:11:18.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,This guy's a civilian. CIA?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:20.91,0:11:24.97,Thought,,0,0,0,,My whole body is trembling, \Nbut it's not fear.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:24.97,0:11:28.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's the thrill of standing on the battlefield \Nbetween life and death.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:42.64,0:11:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't I tell you not to move?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:44.76,0:11:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:57.78,0:12:01.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been a while since I've enjoyed a good hunt.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:01.32,0:12:04.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Cross the river. \NFive meter intervals. Head west.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:04.52,0:12:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep visual contact with each other at all times.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:27.98,0:12:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Count heads.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:31.10,0:12:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We just did.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:33.18,0:12:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,No arguing. Do it again.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:35.59,0:12:36.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:36.57,0:12:38.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,Damn it. He figured me out? {???????}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:42.20,0:12:43.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,Will I make it? {/have enough time}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:52.26,0:12:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We're one man short.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:53.66,0:12:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood. Current position?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:56.31,0:12:58.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Two hundred meters\N in front of the helicopter.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:58.97,0:13:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:00.17,0:13:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire all rockets at that position. {he just designated}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.78,0:13:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But our own men...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:04.93,0:13:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's an order.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:06.62,0:13:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,B-But, sir...
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.80,0:13:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He's done for. {??????}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:11.92,0:14:16.63,Thought,,0,0,0,,Right now, I'm caught up in a vortex \Nof insane ecstasy.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:17.22,0:14:22.80,Thought,,0,0,0,,The same sensation I felt during the crash, \Nat the threshold between life and death.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:48.85,0:15:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Takao...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:51.60,0:15:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm back.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:58.36,0:15:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.13,0:16:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Were you followed?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:01.25,0:16:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Three cars tailed me\N in shifts after I left Tokyo.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:05.72,0:16:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I lost them near the coastal entrance.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:07.92,0:16:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Right. I figured as much.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:11.83,0:16:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Takao...
Dialogue: 10,0:16:22.05,0:16:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When I heard your voice,\N I couldn't believe it.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:25.30,0:16:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But I kept waiting.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:29.10,0:16:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew you'd come back.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:31.81,0:16:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Sachiko...
Dialogue: 10,0:17:10.25,0:17:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Takao!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:23.28,0:17:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsuki will be coming here.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:27.16,0:17:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you going to ask what happened?
Dialogue: 10,0:17:48.73,0:17:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Took you long enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:49.84,0:17:53.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Shaking the tail wasn't easy. \NThis place might already be compromised.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:54.56,0:17:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But man, you look like hell.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:20.71,0:18:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't?!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.73,0:18:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.27,0:18:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A JASDF Phantom was in El Salvador!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:27.30,0:18:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a legitimate bombshell! {great scoop}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:29.48,0:18:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't publish it.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:32.89,0:18:34.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:35.35,0:18:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:37.98,0:18:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What about Taniguchi?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:39.00,0:18:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,He was killed.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:41.60,0:18:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The papers say guerrillas did it. \NHis body was found covered in torture marks.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:48.38,0:18:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And you still won't publish it? {even though a man died for it}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:59.25,0:19:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's the enemy? The CIA?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:01.87,0:19:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The CIA?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:03.46,0:19:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The ones chasing me in El Salvador were CIA.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.03,0:19:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:08.46,0:19:10.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be taking that back.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:10.36,0:19:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you planning?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:12.36,0:19:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not over yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:13.59,0:19:16.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, stop! Don't try to dig any deeper.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:16.97,0:19:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't handle this on our own!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:19.44,0:19:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,A man already died for this!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:23.69,0:19:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You're doing this to avenge Taniguchi?
Dialogue: 10,0:19:27.98,0:19:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm doing it to satisfy what's inside me. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:39.82,0:19:41.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Yazawa Takao.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:41.71,0:19:46.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Former member of the 7th Air Wing \Nat Hyakuri Base, Japan Air Self-Defense Force.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:46.37,0:19:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Last fall, he was injured in a training accident,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:50.27,0:19:54.37,Default,,0,0,0,,hospitalized long-term, \Nand then discharged from the service.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:54.37,0:20:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,His girlfriend, Kikumiya Sachiko, 23. \NLives in an apartment in Setagaya.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.26,0:20:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And the editor-in-chief of the aviation magazine {\i1}Air Journal{\i0}, a man named Matsuki.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:06.10,0:20:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Since returning to Japan, those are the only two people Yazawa has contacted so far, Mr. Vincent.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:17.53,0:20:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What's Yazawa's latest move?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:19.69,0:20:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,He left the hotel after parting\N from the woman.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:22.15,0:20:25.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we're keeping him\N under surveillance.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:26.42,0:20:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Sawada, you'd prefer to let the target \Nrun free a little longer, wouldn't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:31.63,0:20:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:33.00,0:20:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,From our standpoint, we need to apprehend the person behind that photograph first. {???? he says "behind the one in that photo" as if there were two people in the pic and one was standing behind the other, but that pic is from el salvador and the two people in it are standing separately so idk}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:40.89,0:20:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:41.84,0:20:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,As you like it.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:45.34,0:20:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,This is your country, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:58.19,0:21:03.10,Thought,,0,0,0,,After parting with Sachiko,\N I went back to Tokyo and waited for a man.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:08.85,0:21:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:10.02,0:21:14.47,Thought,,0,0,0,,Iwaoka of the 7th Air Wing at Hyakuri Base. \NHe used to be my navigator.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:15.05,0:21:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Long time no see.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:17.74,0:21:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't changed either.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:22.47,0:21:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? So one of our squad's Phantoms \Nshowed up in El Salvador?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:26.55,0:21:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you believe that?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:28.72,0:21:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The bandage on your chest\N says you're not joking. {Was "cast" instead of "bandage", but you cannot put that on your chest}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:32.23,0:21:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And we've had company\N tailing us for a while now.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:41.08,0:21:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do this.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:59.51,0:22:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Dumbass!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:00.72,0:22:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You got a death wish, punk?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:05.86,0:22:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Man, kids these days have no backbone.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:09.31,0:22:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,After you disappeared following the accident, \NI haven't found anyone who can fly with me.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:14.68,0:22:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I bet you pulled that stunt again, didn't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:17.65,0:22:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's the best way to gauge a pilot's skill \Nthe first time you team up.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:23.63,0:22:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,You did the same thing on our first flight.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:26.99,0:22:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You started listing off excuses about feeling sick \Nand all kinds of "malfunctions,"
Dialogue: 10,0:22:31.18,0:22:33.60,Default,,0,0,0,,then just ditched navigating altogether. {??? idk what he means by "accidents"}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:34.25,0:22:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Most guys would panic after that, but not you.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:38.19,0:22:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of freaking out, you just enjoyed \Nflying solo however you liked.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:41.87,0:22:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I say, true fighter pilots like you \Ndon't come around anymore.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:46.27,0:22:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a favor to ask.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:48.77,0:22:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,About that Phantom, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:51.06,0:22:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Dig into the crew of that plane. \NWe're bound to find something.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:00.88,0:23:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it. You be careful too.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:09.60,0:23:11.99,Top,,0,0,0,,Langley's getting impatient.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:11.99,0:23:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,They're demanding the target \Nbe eliminated as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:15.71,0:23:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,This whole thing started with us,\N the CIA and the military, jumping the gun.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:20.06,0:23:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,If this leaks to the opposition, \Nit could even threaten the current administration.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:25.78,0:23:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The White House won't like that, especially with the presidential election coming up.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:31.31,0:23:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What do those thickheaded fools\N in the White House know?
Dialogue: 10,0:23:34.92,0:23:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,They only care about popularity.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:37.31,0:23:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They're afraid of the kind of popular backlash\N that happened during the Vietnam War.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:41.76,0:23:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why they're acting weak. {meaning are very cautious and easy to spook}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:43.58,0:23:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is exactly why we have to rein them in \Nand take control of America ourselves.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:49.07,0:23:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If we secure El Salvador, a key foothold \Nin Central and South America, {lol, lmao even}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:53.18,0:23:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,we'll gain the upper hand in our power game \Nwith the White House.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:57.81,0:23:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't like it.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:59.27,0:24:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:04.93,0:24:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That "Yellow Monkey" mob meddling in our business. {I assume proper name?}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:09.77,0:24:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be helped. \NWe stand out too much in this country.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:13.59,0:24:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And another thing:\N the smell of your cigarettes.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:17.15,0:24:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,At least switch to American smokes \Nwhen you're in my presence.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:21.01,0:24:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure thing.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:22.30,0:24:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, taking out one Jap \Nshould be easy enough.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:25.11,0:24:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:27.41,0:24:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,He survived that rocket barrage.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:31.23,0:24:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He won't go down easy.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:33.24,0:24:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So what's the plan?
Dialogue: 10,0:24:35.41,0:24:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The woman.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:41.21,0:24:44.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Kikumiya-san? Package delivery.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:44.21,0:24:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Coming!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:47.38,0:24:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I just need your seal here.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:08.49,0:25:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, this is {\i1}Air Journal{\i0}.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:11.16,0:25:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,May I speak to Editor-in-Chief Matsuki-san?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:14.46,0:25:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. Matsuki resigned as of yesterday.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:23.71,0:25:26.44,TV,,0,0,0,,In the upcoming US presidential election,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:26.44,0:25:30.17,TV,,0,0,0,,a fierce battle is expected between the incumbent and the challenger.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:46.11,0:25:47.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,Damn it.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:47.69,0:25:49.72,Thought,,0,0,0,,There was another Phantom.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:49.72,0:25:53.16,Thought,,0,0,0,,The Self-Defense Force jet in the foreground \Nwas so striking I overlooked it.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:53.16,0:25:57.62,Thought,,0,0,0,,It wasn't just the Phantom from Hyakuri \Nthat went to El Salvador.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:58.83,0:26:01.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,I contacted Iwaoka at Hyakuri Base.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:01.88,0:26:03.57,Thought,,0,0,0,,But he wasn't there.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:03.57,0:26:08.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,The person who answered instead said there was a message for me and gave me a phone number.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:14.56,0:26:18.23,Thought,,0,0,0,,It was a resort hotel in Nago City, Okinawa.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:18.23,0:26:20.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,After a while, Iwaoka came on the line.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:20.29,0:26:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yazawa?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:21.23,0:26:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Why are you there?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:23.43,0:26:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I found them.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:24.57,0:26:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The pilots of that Phantom \Nare now assigned to my unit!{?? what phantom? if they're on his unit, why go all the way to okinawa? not like everything else in this story makes any sense, but man...}
Dialogue: 10,0:26:27.35,0:26:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,You serious?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:27.96,0:26:31.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I checked the files using the serial number. \NI met with the two of them and persuaded them.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:31.80,0:26:33.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll bring them to you tomorrow.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:33.27,0:26:33.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Where?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:33.90,0:26:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Haneda.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:34.71,0:26:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,JAL Flight 902 arrives at 3:20. {??? jaru no 9*2 bin de}
Dialogue: 10,0:26:50.68,0:26:53.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yazawa-san, I presume?
Dialogue: 10,0:26:53.66,0:26:57.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Sawada from the Cabinet Intelligence Office. {internal affairs}
Dialogue: 10,0:26:57.41,0:27:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how long you wait, \Nthe pilot and navigator aren't coming.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:01.64,0:27:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You abducted them, didn't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:03.62,0:27:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We're only looking for the person who took\N that photograph in El Salvador and sent it to you. {??? again, maybe im gravely misunderstanding things but he says "sent that picture to el salvador" - like if it was taken in jp, what's so special about it?? why send it to el sal if it was taken in jp???}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:08.86,0:27:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll cooperate with us, won't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:12.82,0:27:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Sawada.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:15.78,0:27:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So you tried to get the jump on us?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:20.20,0:27:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,What a shame to meet you here, Mr. Vincent.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:30.42,0:27:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Yazawa, I've been looking forward \Nto seeing you again.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:35.34,0:27:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You came all this way \Njust to settle the score from last time?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:40.27,0:27:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to put a period on this\N as soon as possible.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:43.83,0:27:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Before the presidential election?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:46.19,0:27:49.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? Still sharp as a tack, I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:51.62,0:27:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The one you were really chasing \Nwas the other Phantom.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:55.82,0:28:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,There probably are still several more Phantoms in El Salvador.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:01.91,0:28:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The CIA and the military brought them in.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:04.64,0:28:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But when I got my hands \Non that top-secret information,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:08.35,0:28:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,it created friction between you \Nand the White House.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:10.66,0:28:15.67,Default,,0,0,0,,If that ever went public, it's obvious \Nthe current president would get hammered.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:15.67,0:28:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we need you gone, \Nand that'll be the end of it.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:19.36,0:28:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You think it'll be that easy?
Dialogue: 10,0:28:26.86,0:28:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:40.66,0:28:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Impressive potential.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:43.35,0:28:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe you should recruit him \Nas one of your agents.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:47.62,0:28:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That bus's rigged to blow! {??? I think I hear "that bus is going to explode"}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:49.84,0:28:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Run!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:51.46,0:28:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you're gonna die!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:53.46,0:28:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Move it!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:03.79,0:30:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Shit!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:30.03,0:30:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{??? chikusho?}
Dialogue: 10,0:31:36.67,0:31:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay! Otherwise, it wouldn't be any fun.
Dialogue: 10,0:31:40.13,0:31:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Chase him! {chase shiro? change?}
Dialogue: 10,0:32:20.76,0:32:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Sachiko!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:23.84,0:32:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Takao!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:37.61,0:32:38.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Sachiko!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:41.02,0:32:45.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Yazawa! \NYou've entertained me more than enough! {maybe I've entertained you [by showing you sachiko]}
Dialogue: 10,0:32:45.19,0:32:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,But our game ends here!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:54.24,0:32:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Takao!
Dialogue: 10,0:32:57.16,0:33:00.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,I... I'm the one driving Takao into a corner... {/because of me}
Dialogue: 10,0:33:03.58,0:33:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't do it, Sachiko!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:19.64,0:33:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You would even sacrifice yourself\N to save your man?
Dialogue: 10,0:33:22.90,0:33:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,That Yamato Nadeshiko spirit is beautiful!
Dialogue: 10,0:33:25.11,0:33:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But of course I already anticipated that.
Dialogue: 10,0:34:15.37,0:34:16.60,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sachiko...
Dialogue: 10,0:34:16.60,0:34:18.83,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sachiko! What's going on?
Dialogue: 10,0:34:25.30,0:34:27.50,Thought,,0,0,0,,Stop it, you bastard!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:36.39,0:34:38.39,Thought,,0,0,0,,Stop it, I said!
Dialogue: 10,0:34:54.12,0:34:56.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,No... S-Stop!
Dialogue: 10,0:35:09.22,0:35:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That'll do it. \NThat makes him a murderer.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:13.42,0:35:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,All that's left for him is to slit his wrists.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:35.87,0:35:39.99,Thought,,0,0,0,,I knew immediately who those bodies were.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:39.99,0:35:44.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,It had to be the Phantom's pilot and navigator that were supposed to arrive at Haneda.
Dialogue: 10,0:35:51.34,0:35:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Sachiko!
Dialogue: 10,0:35:59.69,0:36:01.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Sachiko...
Dialogue: 10,0:36:12.42,0:36:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,A stimulant... {stimulant (e.g. psychoactive drugs like methamphetamine, ritalin, etc.)}
Dialogue: 10,0:36:15.20,0:36:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Withdrawal symptoms?
Dialogue: 10,0:36:21.50,0:36:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye, Sachiko.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:27.00,0:36:33.19,TV,,0,0,0,,This evening, in a Setagaya apartment, police discovered the bodies of one woman and two men.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:33.19,0:36:35.99,TV,,0,0,0,,Authorities have identified \Nthe suspect as Yazawa Takao, 30,
Dialogue: 10,0:36:35.99,0:36:40.09,TV,,0,0,0,,a former Japan Air Self-Defense Force member\N and the woman's common-law husband,
Dialogue: 10,0:36:40.09,0:36:42.02,TV,,0,0,0,,and issued a nationwide warrant for his arrest.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:42.03,0:36:44.30,TV,,0,0,0,,Drug paraphernalia believed\N to have been used
Dialogue: 10,0:36:44.30,0:36:48.12,TV,,0,0,0,,for stimulants was found\N in a closet in the apartment.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:48.12,0:36:51.14,TV,,0,0,0,,Police believe Yazawa was a habitual user and,
Dialogue: 10,0:36:51.14,0:36:56.98,TV,,0,0,0,,after witnessing his partner's infidelity, \Nlost control and committed the crime.
Dialogue: 10,0:36:59.95,0:37:02.04,Thought,,0,0,0,,I became a fugitive.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:02.45,0:37:05.90,Thought,,0,0,0,,But one question kept gnawing at me:
Dialogue: 10,0:37:06.41,0:37:11.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,Who was the mastermind that sent \Nthe JASDF Phantom to El Salvador? {no clue how that matters now or what's unclear about it}
Dialogue: 10,0:37:13.04,0:37:17.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,Without a doubt, \Nit was a message from Iwaoka to me.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:17.97,0:37:24.05,Thought,,0,0,0,,318... That was our old combination, \Naircraft number 318.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:30.38,0:37:35.68,Thought,,0,0,0,,I laid low at the location indicated in the ad \Nand waited for Iwaoka's next contact.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:38.11,0:37:40.70,Thought,,0,0,0,,On the seventh day, a message arrived.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:45.62,0:37:48.32,Thought,,0,0,0,,It pointed to a certain place.
Dialogue: 10,0:37:49.13,0:37:55.72,Thought,,0,0,0,,A small island about ten kilometers south \Nof a remote islet southwest of Oshima.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:06.01,0:38:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We're sorry, Yazawa!
Dialogue: 10,0:38:12.14,0:38:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It was all our fault.
Dialogue: 10,0:38:45.74,0:38:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This is...
Dialogue: 10,0:39:01.45,0:39:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,A Phantom.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:08.08,0:39:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Sawada-san, I presume? {throwback to 26:50}
Dialogue: 10,0:39:09.51,0:39:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And you are?
Dialogue: 10,0:39:10.49,0:39:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Matsuki, the man you've been chasing. {the editor-in-chief}
Dialogue: 10,0:39:14.29,0:39:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's get to the point.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:15.62,0:39:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Be at the Hotel Plaza, 40th floor, \Nroom 4022, at 3 PM sharp today.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:20.69,0:39:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We have the information you want.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:23.79,0:39:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this about? {/what do yo mean}
Dialogue: 10,0:39:25.63,0:39:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yazawa and Iwaoka will be there too. \NJust you and Vincent, no one else.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:30.37,0:39:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? I see. And what guarantee \Ndo we have that Yazawa will show?
Dialogue: 10,0:39:35.14,0:39:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that I know your name and Vincent's.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:37.93,0:39:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the only one who could know them, right?
Dialogue: 10,0:39:40.46,0:39:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll be waiting.
Dialogue: 10,0:39:58.25,0:40:01.25,Thought,,0,0,0,,It all started with that accident.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:10.18,0:40:14.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,While I was hospitalized \Nfor six months after the crash,
Dialogue: 10,0:40:14.40,0:40:18.06,Thought,,0,0,0,,Iwaoka, who escaped with only minor injuries, \Ncame up with a plan.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:18.06,0:40:23.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,He'd exploit the fact that the Self-Defense Forces covered up accidents that didn't affect civilians.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:23.30,0:40:28.26,Thought,,0,0,0,,They'd disguise a forced landing as an accident \Nand sell the affected Phantom to another country. {not JSDF, Iwaoka would - not sure if that's clear enough, even more unsure how they're supposed to pull that off}
Dialogue: 10,0:40:28.26,0:40:30.53,Thought,,0,0,0,,Matsuki got on board with the plan.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:32.99,0:40:38.15,Thought,,0,0,0,,During a magazine assignment, Matsuki met\N the international arms dealer Daniel Hennimus {?? weird name and can't hear well}
Dialogue: 10,0:40:38.15,0:40:39.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,and pitched the plan to him.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:40.44,0:40:43.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,Hennimus agreed to back them.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:43.91,0:40:49.84,Thought,,0,0,0,,They found a pilot and navigator at Hyakuri Base\N who were struggling financially and bribed them.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:49.84,0:40:51.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,The plan went off without a hitch.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:51.88,0:40:54.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,But there was one unexpected pitfall:
Dialogue: 10,0:40:54.54,0:40:59.38,Thought,,0,0,0,,the Salvadoran government that bought it \Nnever fully repainted the Phantom.
Dialogue: 10,0:40:59.38,0:41:05.86,Thought,,0,0,0,,Until Matsuki saw that photo, he never even imagined it was the very jet they had sold. {?????? how does that make sense? what difference does it make that it's the very same phantom? didn't matsuki show him that picture first? what does it have with the whole wild goose chase matsuki started?????}
Dialogue: 10,0:41:12.27,0:41:14.24,Default,,0,0,0,,All systems ready for takeoff.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:14.24,0:41:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:15.71,0:41:19.59,Thought,,0,0,0,,Matsuki and Iwaoka wept \Nwhen they learned of Sachiko's death. {?????}
Dialogue: 10,0:41:19.59,0:41:23.17,Thought,,0,0,0,,I forgave them. \NNo amount of regret would bring her back.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:36.05,0:41:39.23,Thought,,0,0,0,,They were my best friends, \Nbound to me by the sky.
Dialogue: 10,0:41:39.23,0:41:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Takeoff!
Dialogue: 10,0:42:18.77,0:42:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Correct three degrees right.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:21.02,0:42:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:22.01,0:42:26.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Altitude seventy. \NWeapons system set on. All green!
Dialogue: 10,0:42:26.18,0:42:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:27.23,0:42:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Twelve o'clock.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:28.93,0:42:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Target in sight!
Dialogue: 10,0:42:29.91,0:42:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:41.88,0:42:44.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Sawada-san and Mr. Vincent?
Dialogue: 10,0:42:48.59,0:42:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. So that's how it is?
Dialogue: 10,0:42:51.70,0:42:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You're alone?
Dialogue: 10,0:42:53.81,0:42:56.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We keep our promises.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:56.18,0:42:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yazawa and Iwaoka will be here soon.
Dialogue: 10,0:42:58.48,0:43:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we'll wait.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:08.94,0:43:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Forty seconds till guns are in range.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:10.65,0:43:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:11.41,0:43:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Sight on.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:12.94,0:43:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Vulcan cannon standing by.\N Safety lock open!
Dialogue: 10,0:43:16.41,0:43:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:29.69,0:43:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems they're not coming.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:32.73,0:43:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll be here.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:37.02,0:43:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, restroom.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:54.28,0:43:55.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Twenty seconds. {?????? no clue at all, sounds like something in english?}
Dialogue: 10,0:43:56.28,0:43:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a straight shot now. {????}\NMaintain course, straight ahead.
Dialogue: 10,0:43:59.54,0:44:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 10,0:44:00.74,0:44:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:10.13,0:44:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We're in danger!
Dialogue: 10,0:44:26.82,0:44:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Fire!
Dialogue: 10,0:45:11.19,0:45:12.04,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:45:19.53,0:45:20.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? What's going on?
Dialogue: 10,0:45:20.99,0:45:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:46:08.33,0:46:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Iwaoka.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:09.50,0:46:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 10,0:46:11.96,0:46:14.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Flying this stiffly doesn't suit us. {????}
Dialogue: 10,0:46:15.36,0:46:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,My thoughts exactly. Ready?
Dialogue: 10,0:46:17.13,0:46:18.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, let's do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:46:20.09,0:46:23.46,TV,,0,0,0,,The White House announced today that, \Nat the President's direction, {????? can't hear shit}
Dialogue: 10,0:46:23.46,0:46:28.20,TV,,0,0,0,,the United States has expanded military aid \Nto the Salvadoran government,
Dialogue: 10,0:46:28.20,0:46:32.62,TV,,0,0,0,,including the introduction \Nof F-4 Phantom fighter jets.
Dialogue: 10,0:46:32.62,0:46:36.61,TV,,0,0,0,,The opposition is expected \Nto respond with heavy criticism,
Dialogue: 10,0:46:36.61,0:46:38.28,TV,,0,0,0,,and in the upcoming presidential election,
Dialogue: 10,0:46:38.28,0:46:42.07,TV,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1000)}the issue is likely to become a major point of contention.
